# Tripify Database Business Rules

## Purpose

Define the business rules that must be respected when reading and writing data in the database.

This document is focused on system behavior, not UI behavior.

---

# Core Entities

## User
Represents an authenticated application user.

### Rules
- A user is identified internally by `id`.
- A user is linked to Supabase auth by `supabaseAuthId`.
- `email` must be unique.
- `supabaseAuthId` must be unique.
- `provider` is `GOOGLE`.
- User record is created or updated after successful auth verification.

---

## Trip
Represents a travel plan created by a user.

### Rules
- A trip has exactly one owner.
- `ownerId` must reference an existing user.
- `title` is required.
- `destination` is required.
- `travelerCount` must be at least 1.
- `startDate` must be before or equal to `endDate`.
- `timezone` defaults to `Asia/Bangkok`.
- A trip may be published as a template using `isTemplatePublished`.

### Status rules
Allowed statuses:
- `DRAFT`
- `ACTIVE`
- `COMPLETED`
- `ENDED_EARLY`
- `ARCHIVED`
- `CANCELLED`

### Trip completion rules
- Only owner can change a trip to `COMPLETED` or `ENDED_EARLY`.
- When trip is ended:
  - `status` must be updated
  - `endedAt` must be set

---

## TripMember
Represents membership of a user in a trip.

### Rules
- A user can appear only once per trip.
- `(tripId, userId)` must be unique.
- The owner must also exist in `TripMember`.
- Valid roles:
  - `OWNER`
  - `MEMBER`

### Membership creation rules
- When a trip is created:
  - create owner membership automatically
- When invitation is accepted:
  - create member if not already exists

---

## TripDay
Represents one day inside a trip.

### Rules
- A trip day belongs to one trip.
- `(tripId, dayNumber)` must be unique.
- `dayNumber` starts from 1 and increments by 1.
- Days should represent the full trip date range from `startDate` to `endDate`.

### Creation rules
- Trip days are generated automatically when a trip is created.
- Day generation must include both start and end date.

---

## ItineraryItem
Represents a planned activity inside a trip day.

### Rules
- An itinerary item belongs to one trip day.
- `title` is required.
- `sortOrder` is used for ordering inside the day.
- `estimatedCost` must be non-negative if provided.
- `isCompleted` defaults to `false`.

### Ownership / access rules
- A user can create/update/delete itinerary items only if they are part of the trip.

---

## TripInvitation
Represents an invitation to join a trip.

### Rules
- An invitation belongs to one trip.
- An invitation has exactly one inviter.
- An invitation may target:
  - `inviteeUserId`
  - or `inviteeEmail`
- At least one of those two fields must be present.

### Status rules
Allowed statuses:
- `PENDING`
- `ACCEPTED`
- `DECLINED`
- `EXPIRED`
- `REVOKED`
- `CANCELLED`

### Invitation creation rules
- Only trip owner can create invitation.
- Invitation starts with `PENDING`.

### Invitation acceptance rules
- Only intended invitee can accept invitation.
- Invitation must still be `PENDING`.
- On acceptance:
  - set status to `ACCEPTED`
  - set `respondedAt`
  - create `TripMember` if not already exists

### Invitation decline rules
- Only intended invitee can decline invitation.
- Invitation must still be `PENDING`.
- On decline:
  - set status to `DECLINED`
  - set `respondedAt`

---

## Rating
Represents a rating for a completed trip.

### Rules
- A rating belongs to one user and one trip.
- `(userId, tripId)` must be unique.
- `score` must be between 1 and 5.
- `comment` is optional.

### Rating creation rules
- User must be a member of the trip.
- Trip must have status:
  - `COMPLETED`
  - or `ENDED_EARLY`
- A user can rate a trip only once.

---

# Template Rules

## Simple Template Model
A template is not a separate entity.
A template is a normal trip where:

- `isTemplatePublished = true`

Optional supporting fields:
- `templatePublishedAt`
- `templateUseCount`

### Publishing rules
- Only trip owner can publish a trip as a template.
- Publishing sets:
  - `isTemplatePublished = true`
  - `templatePublishedAt = now()`

### Listing rules
- Templates are queried from trips where `isTemplatePublished = true`.

### Clone rules
Cloning a template creates a new trip.

The new trip must:
- have current user as owner
- create owner membership
- copy trip basic information
- copy trip days
- copy itinerary items

The new trip must NOT copy:
- members
- invitations
- ratings

After successful clone:
- increment `templateUseCount` on source trip

---

# Auth Rules

## User sync rules
After backend verifies Supabase token:
- find local user by `supabaseAuthId`
- update if exists
- create if not exists

### Synced fields
- `supabaseAuthId`
- `email`
- `fullName`
- `avatarUrl`
- `providerSubject`

---

# Access Control Rules

## Trip Access
A user can access trip detail only if:
- they are the owner
- or they are a trip member

## Trip Mutation
Only trip owner can:
- update trip basic info
- end trip
- publish template
- create invitations

## Itinerary Access
Trip owner and trip members can:
- read trip days
- read itinerary items
- create/update/delete itinerary items

## Rating Access
Trip owner and trip members can:
- read ratings

Trip members can create rating only after trip ended.

---

# Query Ordering Rules

## Trip detail
- order days by `dayNumber asc`
- order itinerary items by `sortOrder asc`

## Invitations
- newest first by `createdAt desc`

## Ratings
- newest first by `createdAt desc`

## Templates
Suggested default ordering:
- newest published first
- or highest `templateUseCount` first

---

# Deletion / Cascade Rules

## Trip deletion
If trip deletion is supported, it should cascade to:
- trip members
- trip days
- itinerary items
- invitations
- ratings

## Trip day deletion
If trip day deletion is supported, it should cascade to itinerary items.

## User deletion
If user deletion is ever supported later, review cascade behavior carefully.
For current scope, user deletion does not need to be implemented.

---

# Date and Time Rules

## System timezone
- Default business timezone: `Asia/Bangkok`

## Storage rule
- Store dates/times as UTC-compatible database values
- Convert to display timezone on frontend

## Trip day generation
- Trip days should be generated from date boundaries
- Day count should match date span inclusively

---

# Required Integrity Guarantees

## Unique constraints
- `User.supabaseAuthId`
- `User.email`
- `TripMember(tripId, userId)`
- `Rating(userId, tripId)`

## Required foreign key consistency
- every `Trip.ownerId` must point to `User`
- every `TripDay.tripId` must point to `Trip`
- every `ItineraryItem.tripDayId` must point to `TripDay`
- every `TripInvitation.tripId` must point to `Trip`
- every `TripInvitation.inviterId` must point to `User`
- every `Rating.tripId` must point to `Trip`
- every `Rating.userId` must point to `User`

---

# Domain Invariants

These must always remain true:

1. Every trip has exactly one owner.
2. Every owner must also appear in `TripMember`.
3. A user cannot appear twice in the same trip membership list.
4. A user cannot rate the same trip twice.
5. A template is always just a trip with `isTemplatePublished = true`.
6. Cloning a template creates a new independent trip.
7. Invitations do not directly create membership until accepted.
8. Completed or ended-early trips are the only trips that can be rated.